HEADWORD: Peninsula
<hw>Pen*in"su*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peninsula</ets> or <ets>paeninsula</ets>; <ets>paene</ets> almost +
<ets>insula</ets> an island. See <er>Isle</er>.]</ety> <def>A portion of
land nearly surrounded by water, and connected with a larger body by a
neck, or isthmus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peninsular</ent>⟦br⟧
